<subSubSection id="C3163FFFFFD28E08FF7DFA00FC2EF8CF" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="592" pageId="5" pageNumber="590" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BB36C74FFD28E0AFF7DFA00FD7FF8D8" blockId="5.[151,1437,1519,1941]" pageId="5" pageNumber="590">
<emphasis id="B978B066FFD28E0AFF7DFA00FE4CF9D4" bold="true" box="[199,416,1519,1545]" pageId="5" pageNumber="590">Description. Male</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="133770F1FFD28E0AFE09FA00FDF6F9D7" box="[435,538,1519,1546]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1448,1472]" captionTargetBox="[164,1422,416,1422]" captionTargetId="figure-71@5.[156,1431,414,1422]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 5. Habitus photographs Polycomus exspiravit sp. nov. A. Male. B. Female. Scale bar: 2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6417211" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6417211/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="590">Figs. 5A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="133770F1FFD28E0AFD90FA00FD79F9D4" box="[554,661,1519,1545]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1862,1886]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,237,1836]" captionTargetId="figure-43@6.[151,1435,179,1836]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 6. Polycomus exspiravit sp. nov. A. Lateral view of male. B. Lateral view of female. C. Male tegmen. D. Female tegmen. E. face in anterior view. F. Female ovipositor in lateral view. Scale bar: 0.5mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6417219" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6417219/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="590">6A, C, E</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="133770F1FFD28E0AFD1EFA00FD26F9D4" box="[676,714,1519,1545]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1426,1450]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,181,1402]" captionTargetId="figure-19@7.[152,1435,181,1402]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 7. Habitus (alive) of Polycomus exspiravit sp. nov. on leaf. A. Male. B. Female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6417223" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6417223/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="590">7A</figureCitation>
). Body size small, pubescent. Head small, slightly wider than the anterior margin of pronotum. Frontal rostrum slightly narrower than antennal scape. Eyes large and laterally protruding. Clypeus narrow and apically straight. Labrum shield-like, medially bumped, and apically concaved. Three apical joints of maxillary palpi distinctly elongated, fifth joint apically truncated. Pronotum transverse. Anterior margin straight, and the posterior slightly sinuate. The posterior conspicuously wider than the anterior. Tegmina pubescent. Six primary veins staggered with many transverse veins. The visible part of hindwings is half of the tegmina length. Internal tympanum large and shaped as long-oval, and external tympanum replaced by a pit. Hind tibia bearing three pairs of dorsal spurs.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB36C74FFD28E0AFF7DF8E0FC4FF848" blockId="5.[151,1437,1519,1941]" pageId="5" pageNumber="590">
<emphasis id="B978B066FFD28E0AFF7DF8E0FED9F8F4" bold="true" box="[199,309,1807,1833]" pageId="5" pageNumber="590">Genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="133770F1FFD28E0AFEF3F8E0FE29F8F4" box="[329,453,1807,1833]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1960,1984]" captionTargetBox="[166,1391,739,1930]" captionTargetId="figure-222@4.[160,1427,739,1934]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4. Male genitalia. A–C. Trigonidium rubrumoculus sp. nov. D–F. Polycomus exspiravit sp. nov. A, D. Dorsal view. B, E. Lateral view. C, F. Ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6417207" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6417207/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="590">Fig. 4D–F</figureCitation>
). Epiphallic median lobe scimitar-like and bearing apex curved outwards. Epiphallic lateral lobe almost rectangular-like, armed with truncated apex and significantly wider than the median lobe. Ectoparamere is partially membranous and partially sclerotized. Membranous portion enormously expanded and sclerotized part sickle-like, curved inward with somewhat blunt apex.
</paragraph>
