<paragraph id="8BB36C74FFD08E08FF7DFA37FB04FA2F" blockId="7.[151,1437,1496,1883]" box="[199,1256,1496,1523]" pageId="7" pageNumber="592">
<emphasis id="B978B066FFD08E08FF7DFA37FEF2FA2F" bold="true" box="[199,286,1496,1522]" pageId="7" pageNumber="592">Female</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="133770F1FFD08E08FE94FA37FE63FA2E" box="[302,399,1496,1523]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1448,1472]" captionTargetBox="[164,1422,416,1422]" captionTargetId="figure-71@5.[156,1431,414,1422]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 5. Habitus photographs Polycomus exspiravit sp. nov. A. Male. B. Female. Scale bar: 2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6417211" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6417211/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="592">Figs. 5B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="133770F1FFD08E08FE21FA37FE10FA2E" box="[411,508,1496,1523]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1862,1886]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,237,1836]" captionTargetId="figure-43@6.[151,1435,179,1836]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 6. Polycomus exspiravit sp. nov. A. Lateral view of male. B. Lateral view of female. C. Male tegmen. D. Female tegmen. E. face in anterior view. F. Female ovipositor in lateral view. Scale bar: 0.5mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6417219" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6417219/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="592">6B, D, F</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="133770F1FFD08E08FDB2FA36FDC0FA2E" box="[520,556,1497,1523]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1426,1450]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,181,1402]" captionTargetId="figure-19@7.[152,1435,181,1402]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 7. Habitus (alive) of Polycomus exspiravit sp. nov. on leaf. A. Male. B. Female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6417223" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6417223/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="592">7B</figureCitation>
). Resemble male but colored lighter. Ovipositor blade-shaped.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB36C74FFD08E08FF7DFA13FEB5F917" blockId="7.[151,1437,1496,1883]" pageId="7" pageNumber="592">
<emphasis id="B978B066FFD08E08FF7DFA13FEA3F9CB" bold="true" box="[199,335,1532,1558]" pageId="7" pageNumber="592">Coloration.</emphasis>
The body is a yellowish-brown color. At the occiput, there are an irregular dark brown pattern. The scape of the antenna is brown. In the front perspective, the face has motifs as double wings. Pronotic plate with three pairs of dark spots on a pale background. Pronotum's lateral margin is dark brown. Tegmina with many dark brown spots and discontinuous dark brown patches on the lateral portion. Blackish brown on the visible area of the hindwings. Sternite with a severing pattern of uniform black spots. The apical portion of the ovipositor of females is reddish brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB36C74FFD08E08FF7DF93BFC2EF8CF" blockId="7.[151,1437,1496,1883]" pageId="7" pageNumber="592">
<emphasis id="B978B066FFD08E08FF7DF93BFE92F933" bold="true" box="[199,382,1748,1774]" pageId="7" pageNumber="592">Measurements.</emphasis>
Male (n=5). BL 5.11±1.06, PL 0.67±0.12, TL 3.73±0.63, HFL 3.56±0.60. Female (n=5). BL 5.31±1.23, PL 0.75±0.14, TL 3.90±0.54, HFL 3.66±0.41, OL 1.98±0.28.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3163FFFFFD08E08FF7DF8F3FAF8F8EA" box="[199,1300,1820,1847]" pageId="7" pageNumber="592" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BB36C74FFD08E08FF7DF8F3FAF8F8EA" blockId="7.[151,1437,1496,1883]" box="[199,1300,1820,1847]" pageId="7" pageNumber="592">
<emphasis id="B978B066FFD08E08FF7DF8F3FEA2F8EB" bold="true" box="[199,334,1820,1846]" pageId="7" pageNumber="592">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name refers that the vertex of the new species resembles a painted face (
<figureCitation id="133770F1FFD08E08FB0AF8F3FAEBF8EA" box="[1200,1287,1820,1847]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1862,1886]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,237,1836]" captionTargetId="figure-43@6.[151,1435,179,1836]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 6. Polycomus exspiravit sp. nov. A. Lateral view of male. B. Lateral view of female. C. Male tegmen. D. Female tegmen. E. face in anterior view. F. Female ovipositor in lateral view. Scale bar: 0.5mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6417219" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6417219/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="592">Fig. 6E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
